President Biden and Prime Minister Modi of India have affirmed a vision of the United States and India as close partners in the world. They emphasized the importance of trust and mutual understanding in their Comprehensive Global and Strategic Partnership. The leaders highlighted the role of technology in deepening their partnership, particularly through the Initiative on Critical and Emerging Technology. They also expressed a commitment to space cooperation, defense partnership, clean energy transition, and economic cooperation. The leaders emphasized the importance of democracy, human rights, and inclusivity in their partnership. They pledged to work together to address global challenges such as terrorism, climate change, and regional conflicts. Overall, the leaders expressed their commitment to a broad and deep bilateral relationship that promotes peace, prosperity, and shared values.